	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-11234" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-11234" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/92f976a1ebcf73627230faefcdb8f0c8?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='https://plus.google.com/115385772879706240472' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Gihan Subhashana</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2012/making-a-custom-control-for-the-theme-customizer/comment-page-1/#comment-11234">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2012-09-16T04:31:38+00:00">September 16, 2012 at 4:31 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Hi,</p>
<p>Thanks you very much for your tutorial.</p>
<p>I tried to use Jquery UI slider inside a customize controller. But it doesn&#8217;t load jquery ui and I&#8217;m getting &#8220;Uncaught TypeError: Object [object Object] has no method &#8216;slider&#8217;&#8221; in JS console.</p>
<p>Here is my code.<br />
<code><br />
class Slider_Control extends WP_Customize_Control{<br />
	public $type = 'slider';</p>
<p>	public function render_content(){<br />
		?&gt;</p>
<p>			label); ?&gt;<br />
			Value: value; ?&gt;<br />
			&lt;input type=&quot;hidden&quot; value=&quot;value; ?&gt;" /&gt;</p>
<p>			jQuery(function(){<br />
				jQuery('.slider').slider();<br />
			});</p>
<p>		&lt;?php<br />
	}<br />
}</p>
<p>and action in function.php to load jquery ui<br />
function my_admin_scripts(){<br />
	wp_enqueue_script(&#039;jquery-ui-slider&#039;);<br />
}<br />
add_action(&#039;admin_enqueue_scripts&#039;, &#039;my_admin_scripts&#039;);<br />
</code></p>
<p>Any help is highly appreciate. </p>
<p>Thanks.</p>
</div>

