	<li class="comment even depth-2 parent" id="comment-11386" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-11386" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3f2bfad6bac969c8cf6624a7d4bc56eb?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name">Sander</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2012/making-a-custom-control-for-the-theme-customizer/comment-page-1/#comment-11386">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2012-11-13T09:28:05+00:00">November 13, 2012 at 9:28 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>I actually build a module to recompile CSS when needed, using the LESS CSS framework. After saving the settings from the Live Designer, my module will run a recompile with the new variables from the database. So the CSS is only generated when changes have been made. And I don&#8217;t write the CSS to a file, I use wp_register_style to serve up a .php file, that will output the new CSS or a 304 not modified.</p>
<p>Works like a charm!</p>
</div>

