	<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0994d5e2e158a24ba8017c2525d78263?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://ottodestruct.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Otto</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2012/making-a-custom-control-for-the-theme-customizer/comment-page-1/#comment-11777">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2013-04-18T11:27:53+00:00">April 18, 2013 at 11:27 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>The get_theme_mod function can take two parameters. The first is the name of the theme-mod to get, the second can be a default value.</p>
<p>So, get_theme_mod(&#8216;example&#8217;, &#8216;default&#8217;) will return &#8220;default&#8221; if the example setting does not exist.</p>
</div>

